Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the application of Agile Software Engineering Methodologies principles and values in ICT Governance projects. 
- cs.IT (Information Technology) is also likely as the paper focuses on the convergence between ICT and business. 
- cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are possible categories as the paper mentions the Critical Success Factors (CSF) of ICT Governance projects, which may include security and privacy considerations. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is a less likely category, but it is possible as the paper proposes a reference model for Agile Governance in ICT, which may involve multiple agents or stakeholders.
